description.plain:
Ari David Starace (b. July 27, 1994), better known by his stage name Y2K, is a self proclaimed “professional sellout” and the “best producer in the world” coming out of Scottsdale, Arizona. He started making music in 2015.

Y2K is best known for producing “Lalala” by himself and Canadian-Armenian rapper bbno$. He is also known for producing songs by Doja Cat, Ariana Grande, KILLY, and others.
